2006 Ravensdale Cumberland Road Race
description: 2006 Ravensdale-Cumberland Road Race presented by FSA/Vision 4 Corners Cycling and The Starbucks Duetto Visa
course: Rolling loop in rural southeast King County.  Circuit loop is 28 miles in length and features one short (0.15 mile), steep (+20%) climb, 39x25 or higher recommended.  Staging and finish is at Tahoma Jr HS just outside of Maple Valley.  Approximate 2 mile neutral rollout.  Finish is approximately 4 miles from entry to circuit with a climb approximately 1 mile from the finish.  Course map is available at www.vision4corners.com.  Women 4 will do one lap of the circuit loop, all others will do two laps of the circuit with the Men Pro 1/2 also doing one additional lap of the Ravensdale Circuit (9 miles).
registration: Pre and race day registration: $ 20.  Preregistration through www.Active.com (additional fee) or send completed USCF Release including WSBA number in upper right corner with check to:  Michael Kopp-4 Corners Cycling, PO Box 873, Maple Valley, WA  98038.  Mail in registration must be postmarked by Friday, June 30.  On-line registration closes Friday, July 7.  All riders will need to have signed USCF Release and show current USCF license at registration.  Only Women 4 and Men 5 may purchase one day USCF licenses.  WSBA rental numbers will be available.  Registration opens at 7:30 am and closes 20 minutes prior to the start time for the respective field.
notes: Promoter may combine fields.  Master A/B and Masters C/D will be a combined field but scored separately.  WSBA numbers on both sides along with WSBA frame number. Feed Zone is at BPA Power Substation on Retreat Kanaskat Rd approximately 6 miles from Tahoma Jr HS.  No other feeding is allowed on course. USA Cycling rules apply.  Approved helmets must be worn.
directions: From I-405 north/south take exit # 4 to SR 169-Maple Valley Highway.  Proceed southeast (towards Maple Valley and Enumclaw) on SR 169 approximately 14 miles to the intersection of SR 169 and SR 516 Kent Kangley Rd (4 Corners).  Left onto Kent Kangley (eastbound).  Proceed approximately 1/4 mile then left on Summit-Landsburg Rd.  Proceed approximately one mile to Tahoma Jr HS on the left side of Summit-Landsburg Rd.  Parking at Tahoma Jr. HS will be shared with Common Ground Church.  Parking is only in the area designated for \\\"Bike Race\\\".
